    "recommendations": [
      "catch (err) and inspect err.code; emit kind 'settings-file-missing' only on ENOENT, otherwise 'settings-file-unreadable' with the OS-level message. T-015 specifies a missing-file fixture so it would still pass; an additional unreadable-file scenario is not currently covered.",
      "Bind the error (catch (err)) and either include err.message in the warning, or branch on err.code to emit distinct warning kinds for ENOENT vs EACCES vs EISDIR. At minimum, append `: ${err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err)}` to the message field, mirroring the pattern already used a few lines below for JSON.parse failures."
    ],
    "descriptions": [
      "Any failure of fs.readFileSync — EACCES, EISDIR, EMFILE — is reported as 'settings-file-missing'. The kind suggests an absent file; the underlying cause may be a permission error on a present file. The error object is discarded (catch with no binding), so users have no signal to diagnose.",
      "The catch around fs.readFileSync(settingsPath, 'utf8') has no err binding and unconditionally returns the 'settings-file-missing' warning. EACCES (settings.json owned by another user / chmod 000), EISDIR (settings.json is a directory), ENOTDIR (~/.claude is a file), and any other I/O failure all surface as 'Settings file not found'."
    ],
    "impacts": [
      "If ~/.claude/settings.json exists but is unreadable for the running process, the user sees 'settings file not found' and is told to enable a plugin that may already be enabled. This is a soft correctness regression of the contract's 'structured note' obligation in line 17 of contract.md ('returns false with a structured note').",
      "The student cannot diagnose why the learning-output-style plugin is not detected. They see 'file not found' and create the file, but the real problem is permissions or a typo elsewhere in the path. Because outputStyleOk is advisory in cycle 1, the consequence is mild now, but the same probe is the load-bearing input to the AC-1.3 invariant in later cycles."
    ],
    "evidence": "  try {\n    raw = fs.readFileSync(settingsPath, 'utf8');\n  } catch {\n    return {\n      ok: false,\n      warning: {\n        kind: 'settings-file-missing',\n        message: `Settings file not found at ${settingsPath}`,\n      },\n    };\n  }",
