      "T-031 spies on fs.readFileSync, fs.readFile, and fsPromises.readFile, then asserts every observed read path resolves to <home>/.claude/settings.json. It does not spy on fs.createReadStream, fs.open{Sync}, fsPromises.open, or fs.readv. An implementer using e.g. `const fd = fs.openSync(somePath, 'r'); fs.readSync(fd, ...)` to read a different file would not be caught. Also, `expect(observedPaths.length).toBeGreaterThan(0)` ensures at least one read happened, but does not enforce exactly one — a probe that read settings.json AND another path via the spied APIs would fail the per-path assertion (good), but a probe that read another path via createReadStream and settings.json via readFileSync would still pass."
