    "categories": [
      "security"
    ],
    "recommendations": [
      "Add z.string().refine((p) => path.isAbsolute(p), { message: 'projectRoot must be absolute' }) to the start tool schema. Cheap, non-breaking, and prevents an entire class of CWD-confusion bugs in future cycles."
    ],
    "descriptions": [
      "The tool's zod schema declares projectRoot as z.string() with the description 'Absolute path to the project root', but neither the schema nor runStart enforces path.isAbsolute(projectRoot). A relative projectRoot like '../../../etc' would be path.join'd with 'paths' and resolved against the MCP server's CWD at the time of invocation, potentially scanning a directory outside the intended project. The blast radius is bounded — scanRegistry only reads path.json files inside the chosen root and emits warnings, so the worst case is a confused-deputy disclosure of any path.json files reachable from the resolved location."
    ],
    "impacts": [
      "Negligible in cycle 1 — the only caller is the course-engine skill, which passes the actual project root. Becomes load-bearing in later cycles if more tools are added that act on projectRoot (e.g. preflight shell actions in cycle 2+ per A14's wording)."
    ],
    "evidence": "projectRoot: z.string().describe('Absolute path to the project root'),",
    "confidence_spread": [
      "high"
    ],
    "source_ids": [
      "R6-004"
    ]
  },
